Security:
  ✔ A1  delete dead encryption state in backend/src/utils/secret.ts (randomBytes(32) at top, hardcoded encKey constant, dead signPayload, generateSigningSecret).
  ☐ @decide_later A2  internal API trusts static header. replace internalRoutesAuthMiddleware with HMAC shared-secret between zipup and openresty (or restrict by source IP 172.25.0.x). generate shared secret at install time.
  ☐ A3  encrypt appsTable.secret_key at rest with getEncryptionKey(); decrypt in appKeyAuthMiddleware and attach to c.set("app", ...).
  ✔ A4  fix CSRF check in middlewares.ts (the && chain has dead code). use double-submit cookie pattern with constant-time compare.
  ☐ A5  tls verification is disabled for every domain_updated call in events/event.ts. only disable on the first prewarm attempt per domain, then verify.
  ✘ A6  move refreshStore from in-memory Map to Valkey (172.25.0.3). SET with ex=REFRESH_TTL, DEL for consume. auto-expires, works across restarts.
  ✔ A7  /api/admin/refresh bypasses CSRF. CSRF check now runs before the refresh path, so refresh is gated by double-submit cookie.
  ☐ @decide_later A8  zipup container runs as root in docker-compose.base.yaml. create non-root user in Dockerfile, drop user: root, keep only required caps.
  ☐ A9  @decide_later no rate limiting on /api/admin/login or /api/artifacts/* and /api/deployment/*. add Redis-backed rate limiter. - may be in memory for now as our app is singlel instance.
  ☐ A10 openresty server block has no CSP / X-Frame-Options / Permissions-Policy. add more_set_headers in nginx.conf.
  ✘ A11 default admin password is hardcoded "zipup" in scripts/dbInit.ts. force password change on first login or generate random + print to logs.
  ✔ A12 HaveIBeenPwned call has no timeout in helper.ts. wrap with AbortController + 3s timeout.
  ✔ A13 pwned-password check fails open on network error. keep fail-open policy, but log via getLogger().warn so the outage is visible.

